        </div>
        <h1>Tax Extension 2026: How to File, Deadlines, and What to Know</h1>
        <p class="qa-meta">Updated April 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; For tax year 2025 returns filed in 2026</p>
        <p>A tax extension gives you six additional months to file your federal income tax return, moving your deadline from April 15, 2026 to October 15, 2026. Filing for an extension is free, takes minutes, and is automatically approved — but it does not extend the time to pay any taxes you owe. You must still estimate and pay your 2025 tax liability by April 15 to avoid penalties and interest.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block"
          data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549"
